"```sql\nSELECT \n  COUNT(DISTINCT CASE WHEN PLT < 100 THEN Laboratory.ID END) AS Patients_Lower_Than_Normal,\n  COUNT(DISTINCT CASE WHEN PLT > 400 THEN Laboratory.ID END) AS Patients_Higher_Than_Normal\nFROM \n  Laboratory\nWHERE \n  PLT <= 100 OR PLT >= 400;\n```\n\nThis SQL query counts the number of distinct patients with platelet levels lower than the normal range (PLT < 100) and higher than the normal range (PLT > 400) based on the conditions provided in the evidence. The query uses the `Laboratory` table to find patients with abnormal platelet levels."